{"componentChunkName":"component---node-modules-ocular-gatsby-src-templates-doc-page-markdown-jsx","path":"/docs/api-reference/d3-layout","webpackCompilationHash":"e834afbc63fbedeee57b","result":{"data":{"docBySlug":{"html":"<h1 id=\"d3-force-layout\"><a href=\"#d3-force-layout\" aria-label=\"d3 force layout permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>D3 Force Layout</h1>\n<p align=\"center\">\n  <img src=\"/gatsby/images/layouts/d3.png\" height=\"400\" />\n</p>\n<p>This layout is an integration between <a href=\"https://github.com/d3/d3-force\">d3-force</a> and graph.gl to render the layout in a WebGL context.</p>\n<h2 id=\"configurations\"><a href=\"#configurations\" aria-label=\"configurations permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Configurations</h2>\n<p>You can set the custom configuration to the d3-force layout directed by passing a configuration object when instnatiating the layout object for GraphGL.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>GraphGL\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token operator\">...</span>otherProps<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  layout<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">D3ForceLayout</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      nBodyStrength<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      nBodyDistanceMin<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      nBodyDistanceMax<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h4 id=\"alpha-number-optional\"><a href=\"#alpha-number-optional\" aria-label=\"alpha number optional permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>alpha (Number, optional)</h4>\n<p>The target alpha of the layout for each iteration. If alpha is specified, sets the current alpha to the specified number in the range [0,1]. The default value is 0.3.</p>\n<h4 id=\"resumealpha-number-optional\"><a href=\"#resumealpha-number-optional\" aria-label=\"resumealpha number optional permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>resumeAlpha (Number, optional)</h4>\n<p>The resumeAlpha can be used to “reheat” the simulation during interaction, such as when dragging a node, or to resume the simulation after temporarily pausing the layout.\nThe default value is 0.1.</p>\n<h4 id=\"nbodystrength-number-optional\"><a href=\"#nbodystrength-number-optional\" aria-label=\"nbodystrength number optional permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>nBodyStrength: (Number, optional)</h4>\n<p>We use <a href=\"https://github.com/d3/d3-force#many-body\">many-body</a> as the charge force to apply force applies mutually amongst all nodes. It can be used to simulate gravity (attraction) if the <code class=\"language-text\">nBodyStrength</code> is positive, or electrostatic charge (repulsion) if the <code class=\"language-text\">nBodyStrength</code> is negative.\nThe default value is -900.</p>\n<h4 id=\"nbodydistancemin-number-optional\"><a href=\"#nbodydistancemin-number-optional\" aria-label=\"nbodydistancemin number optional permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>nBodyDistanceMin (Number, optional)</h4>\n<p>Sets the minimum distance between nodes over which this force is considered. If distance is not 'nBodyDistanceMin', returns the current minimum distance, which defaults to 100.</p>\n<h4 id=\"nbodydistancemax-number-optional\"><a href=\"#nbodydistancemax-number-optional\" aria-label=\"nbodydistancemax number optional permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>nBodyDistanceMax (Number, optional)</h4>\n<p>Sets the maximum distance between nodes over which this force is considered. If distance is not 'nBodyDistanceMin', returns the current minimum distance, which defaults to 400.</p>\n<h4 id=\"getcollisionradius-function-optional\"><a href=\"#getcollisionradius-function-optional\" aria-label=\"getcollisionradius function optional permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>getCollisionRadius (Function, optional)</h4>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://github.com/d3/d3-force#collision\">collision force</a> treats nodes as circles with a given radius, rather than points, and prevents nodes from overlapping.  The <code class=\"language-text\">getCollisionRadius</code> expects a function as:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token function-variable function\">getCollisionRadius</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token parameter\">node</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> node<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>collisionRadius</code></pre></div>\n<p>The function will iterated each node and return the raidus for collision detection.\nIf getCollisionRadius is not specified, it defaults to zero radius for all nodes.</p>\n<h2 id=\"source\"><a href=\"#source\" aria-label=\"source permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Source</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/uber/graph.gl/blob/master/src/layouts/d3-force/index.js\">d3-force.js</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/uber/graph.gl/blob/master/stories/basic-layouts/stories.js#L56-L71\">Storybook example</a></li>\n</ul>","timeToRead":2,"excerpt":"D3 Force Layout This layout is an integration between d3-force and graph.gl to render the layout in a WebGL context. Configurations You can…","frontmatter":{"title":"D3 Force Layout","cover":"cover","category":"docs","tags":["default"]}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"relativeLinks":{"../../advanced/custom-layout.md":"/docs/advanced/custom-layout","docs/advanced/custom-layout.md":"/docs/advanced/custom-layout","../../advanced/custom-layout":"/docs/advanced/custom-layout","docs/advanced/custom-layout":"/docs/advanced/custom-layout","../../version-policy.md":"/docs/version-policy","docs/version-policy.md":"/docs/version-policy","../../version-policy":"/docs/version-policy","docs/version-policy":"/docs/version-policy","../../advanced/gallery.md":"/docs/advanced/gallery","docs/advanced/gallery.md":"/docs/advanced/gallery","../../advanced/gallery":"/docs/advanced/gallery","docs/advanced/gallery":"/docs/advanced/gallery","../../README.md":"/docs","docs/README.md":"/docs","../..":"/docs","docs":"/docs","../graph.md":"/docs/api-reference/graph","docs/api-reference/graph.md":"/docs/api-reference/graph","../graph":"/docs/api-reference/graph","docs/api-reference/graph":"/docs/api-reference/graph","../edge-style-flow.md":"/docs/api-reference/edge-style-flow","docs/api-reference/edge-style-flow.md":"/docs/api-reference/edge-style-flow","../edge-style-flow":"/docs/api-reference/edge-style-flow","docs/api-reference/edge-style-flow":"/docs/api-reference/edge-style-flow","../edge.md":"/docs/api-reference/edge","docs/api-reference/edge.md":"/docs/api-reference/edge","../edge":"/docs/api-reference/edge","docs/api-reference/edge":"/docs/api-reference/edge","../edge-style-label.md":"/docs/api-reference/edge-style-label","docs/api-reference/edge-style-label.md":"/docs/api-reference/edge-style-l